05:58.220 --> 06:00.860
conducted on humans in the 20th century.

06:01.180 --> 06:05.760
Unit 731, a secret biological and chemical warfare research

06:05.760 --> 06:09.020
and development program under the Imperial Japanese Army,

06:09.440 --> 06:11.180
was established in Manchuria.

06:11.560 --> 06:14.200
Under the command of General Shiro Ishii,

06:14.200 --> 06:16.420
the unit carried out experiments

06:16.420 --> 06:19.580
that included vivisection on live prisoners

06:19.580 --> 06:22.140
exposed to extreme temperatures,

06:22.600 --> 06:25.980
deliberate infections of plague, cholera, and syphilis,

06:26.300 --> 06:29.960
as well as weapons testing on live human subjects.

06:29.960 --> 06:33.140
One particularly gruesome set of experiments

06:33.140 --> 06:36.300
involved locking prisoners in pressure chambers

06:36.300 --> 06:39.920
and exposing them to extreme barometric changes

06:39.920 --> 06:43.620
to observe how the human body would rupture or collapse.

06:43.920 --> 06:46.940
Every grotesque detail was carefully recorded.

06:47.200 --> 06:51.220
But perhaps the most disturbing part of Unit 731's legacy

06:51.220 --> 06:55.080
